  "id": "BIT-pillow-2026-54060",
  "summary": "Pillow: `FontFile.compile()`: `Image.new()` called without `_decompression_bomb_check()`",
  "details": "Pillow is a Python imaging library. Prior to 12.3.0, PIL/FontFile.py FontFile.compile() assembled per-glyph images into a combined bitmap with Image.new(\"1\", (xsize, ysize)) without calling Image._decompression_bomb_check(), allowing a font to trigger excessive allocation during conversion or saving. This issue is fixed in version 12.3.0.",
